    <item>
      <title>Building JSX-like UI in Zig: Part 4 - Visual Internals Guide</title>
      <link>http://localhost:51816/posts/jsx-zig-part-4/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 08 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:51816/posts/jsx-zig-part-4/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;A visual deep-dive into the layout math, DSL ergonomics, and rendering pipeline&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Introduction
    &lt;div id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Parts 1-3, we built a complete JSX-like UI system. But some concepts benefit from visual explanation. This companion guide provides ASCII diagrams and step-by-step breakdowns of the trickier internals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&amp;rsquo;ll cover:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexbox Math&lt;/strong&gt; - How &lt;code&gt;calcSizes&lt;/code&gt; distributes space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rectangle Insets&lt;/strong&gt; - Padding and margins visually&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DSL Ergonomics&lt;/strong&gt; - Why &lt;code&gt;tupleToSlice&lt;/code&gt; exists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Timing&lt;/strong&gt; - Hold-to-repeat mechanics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Render Pipeline&lt;/strong&gt; - Data flow from nodes to pixels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Flexbox Math: calcSizes
    &lt;div id=&#34;flexbox-math-calcsizes&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#flexbox-math-calcsizes&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;calcSizes&lt;/code&gt; function is the heart of our layout system. It solves: &lt;em&gt;given a container and children (some fixed-size, some flexible), how big should each child be?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
