    <item>
      <title>Building JSX-like UI in Zig: Part 2 - The Renderer and Layout System</title>
      <link>http://localhost:51816/posts/jsx-zig-part-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:51816/posts/jsx-zig-part-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;From virtual nodes to actual pixels: implementing flexbox-like layout in Zig&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;

&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Introduction
    &lt;div id=&#34;introduction&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
    
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a
  href=&#34;./01-introduction-and-architecture.md&#34;&gt;Part 1&lt;/a&gt;, we built the foundation: &lt;code&gt;Node&lt;/code&gt; types, properties, and builder functions. Now we need to turn that abstract tree into actual pixels on screen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Renderer&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Layout&lt;/strong&gt;: Calculating the position and size of each node&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drawing&lt;/strong&gt;: Rendering pixels to the screen&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hit Testing&lt;/strong&gt;: Determining which node the mouse is over&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Event Collection&lt;/strong&gt;: Queuing click events for later processing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s build it step by step, using our counter application as the running example.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
